>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/6/01 9:48:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.hvc.rr.com/tfehlberg/Codil/coolwizard.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in Velks</span><hr size=1> my tactics for this - IF and when it isn;t ever-camped is - I pull more than one I zone, otherwise i just basically root and nuke using Fetter and Draught of Fire - or i tried Rains but root seems to always break on the first wave - so straight DD seems to do better ... i get below 40m or poisoned I immediately zone ... <p><img src=http://home.hvc.rr.com/tfehlberg/Codil/codil.gif></img></br>Life is like a room full of dragons...You never know who is going to eat you first</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/6/01 10:55:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in Velks</span><hr size=1> Velks is a bit crowded usually, but if no one is camping IN the entryway, I have had some success in pulling singles down to the bottom, snaring them at the earliest opportunity, then nuking with draught of fire (or even sunstrike).  There's a little raised pathway that I use as the &quot;runway&quot;, and I'll run to one side of it, nuke, then hop off, run around the spider, get back on the pathway, run to the other side and nuke again... repeat until dead.<br><br>Even with this approach I've taken a couple lumps when running past (about 1/3 to 1/2 of the times), and I've occasionally had to zone, but in general it works pretty well.  Also, without root, you usually don't have to worry about the spiders agroing on others.  However, if the other campers are sitting down and too close to your route... the spiders occasionally get distracted and can't resist taking a bite.<br><br>When the entryway is overcamped, sometimes you can find a corner for root and nuke... but in general that's pretty rough.<br><br>Oh, and manaskin/BoF is virtually required when soloing here.<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneuros.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NeuroS </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/7/01 6:58:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in Velks</span><hr size=1> I was soloing velks last night fairly easily and this is how i did it usually velks is pretty camped. (for this to work u need velks robe or shissar stick)<br><br>make sure epic or skin is up b4 <br><br>1) stun or snare single spider for pull<br>2) snare spider if u havent already<br>3) go to the raidsed walkway  on bottom floor<br>4)root spider .. wlak to other side of runway<br>5) click velk robe(if u hvae shissar stick would probably work too) untill root breaks .. <br>6)back-up re root <br>7)run to other side of walkway <br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  rinse &amp; repeat .. mix in draughst toward the end or to speed things up <br><br><br>with this method it takes a bit longer but u can  pretty much constatnly kill <p>NeuroS T'zzorM <a href=http://thedarkexile.dpn.ch/ target="web"> The Dark Exile</a>  7th Hammer<BR>   "part-time wizard... Full-time IIP II IIVII IIP" <BR>  <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.jsp?num=608  target="web">**PIMPology 101**</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhudaloo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hudaloo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/9/01 7:50:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in Velks</span><hr size=1> When I solo in velks I grab a spider and go down to the &quot;runway&quot; at the bottom. When the spider is coming at you, jump off the runway and the spider will head back to get off the runway, then when he comes at you, get on the ramp and the spider will go back to get back on. Nuke during these intervals. Oh yeah, and snare. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/9/01 11:08:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in Velks</span><hr size=1> Be careful with that ramp on/off method... Even though it is little more than kiting, I believe it is considered a pathing exploit. I saw someone do this years ago with Dvinn in crushbone (at base of trainer hill) jump up on path, then step down. Dvinn's path gave plenty of time to get a spell off. <br><br>Just a word of warning.<br><br>Ryll<br><br>Edit: Oh, that person was warned or banned (cannot remember which) - which is why that story had relevence.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryll</A> at: 9/9/01 11:10:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mordeeve>Mordeeve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/14/01 7:35:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in Velks</span><hr size=1> -Single pull to zone area root and shoot dont try to rain when its nuked and dont bother with the statues as root seems to just slip off them. You will go through a lot of Peridots<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but the exp is awesome. Another good thing is if there is a Tank at the zone and he decides to hop in the fight while yer dancing about.... wait for the aggro to slip and drop a rain on its ass<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Mordeeve Zal'Yothmodok///55th Circle Gnome Wizard</b> <i>///SPIRIT LURKERS//Cazic Thule Server</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="htt